{{Location map-line|lat=67}}
{{kml}}
The '''67th parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 67 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]], about 50&nbsp;km north of the [[Arctic Circle]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[North America]].

At this latitude the [[sun]] is visible for 24 hours, 0 minutes during the [[summer solstice]] and 1 hour, 30 minutes during the [[winter solstice]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 67° north passes through:

